{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ae50cd09b1428afac","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are a research sub-agent. You have WebSearch and WebFetch tools (load them first via ToolSearch with query \"select:WebSearch,WebFetch\" if needed).\n\nRESEARCH ANGLE: Cross-cutting commentary and analysis on the fundamental LIMITS of self-improving AI code systems — synthesizing the verifier requirement, the verification ceiling, reward hacking, and base-model bounding into critical takes.\n\nFind specific, quotable analysis from:\n- Blog posts / essays / academic surveys critically analyzing AlphaEvolve, Darwin Godel Machine, STOP and arguing their gains depend on (a) a strong verifier/eval and (b) a strong base model.\n- Surveys on \"self-improving LLM agents\" or \"recursive self-improvement\" that enumerate the verifier/evaluator dependency as a precondition.\n- Pieces noting the domain restriction: AlphaEvolve only works where solutions are machine-evaluable (math, algorithms, code with metrics), and fails in domains lacking a cheap automatic evaluator.\n- Discussion that without verifiable reward, self-improvement loops degrade / collapse / drift.\n\nRun 5-7 WebSearch queries. Then WebFetch the 5-6 best sources (substack, lesswrong, arxiv surveys, reputable tech analysis). Extract exact wording.\n\nSearch terms: \"AlphaEvolve limitation requires automatic evaluator\", \"self-improving LLM agents survey verifier\", \"recursive self-improvement limits verifier base model\", \"Darwin Godel Machine analysis scaffolding not magic\", \"AlphaEvolve only works machine-evaluable domains\", \"self-improvement loop collapses without verifiable reward\".\n\nOUTPUT: Return a list of 5-10 FALSIFIABLE CLAIMS. Each claim must be:\n- A single concrete factual sentence\n- Followed by the EXACT source URL\n- Followed by a short verbatim quote or close paraphrase supporting it\nDo not pad. Only return claims you actually found support for in fetched pages."},"uuid":"691a3c21-75c9-484f-a7cd-4fff899e2385","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:49.760Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
