the efforts on AlphaEvolve focus on these domains. This constraint means that problems requiring manual experimentation or \"wet-lab\" feedback are currently out of scope for this specific approach.\n\nIn practical terms, enterprises should look first at workflows where \"better\" is a quantifiable number the system can compute – be it latency, cost, error rate or throughput. However, there are potential future directions: LLMs are increasingly capable of scaffolding approximate evaluators from sparse, noisy, or even natural language inputs, where a domain expert can describe what matters in vague terms, and the model can produce an initial, code-executable version of it."],"durationSeconds":8.027052249999716,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"41b6a535-8870-4c45-b956-0887cb36f166","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
