{"parentUuid":"3120aeb4-7450-4ba3-ad54-baecbf5b8ed5","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ae50cd09b1428afac","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01KkFCsmcQpdysPMT1gRzYQB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01E4qFXSwHwmFBECf1CPnJiH","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"self-improvement loop collapses without verifiable reward reward hacking drift"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1056,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2445,"cache_read_input_tokens":12502,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2445,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":51,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcG29tburBiNGHMxQhpb4","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"11ba1554-54d1-414f-adc6-b94c5669e063","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:07.166Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"3120aeb4-7450-4ba3-ad54-baecbf5b8ed5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ae50cd09b1428afac","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SUyEmiUz24sGshzidYHntR","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Darwin Godel Machine analysis scaffolding not magic depends on base model benchmark\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code\",\"url\":\"https://sakana.ai/dgm/\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2505.22954\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML\",\"url\":\"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine\"},{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Improvement via Recursive Code Mutation and Empirical Fitness | by Adnan Masood, PhD. | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@adnanmasood/the-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-open-ended-improvement-via-recursive-code-mutation-and-empirical-fitness-a777681d73e4\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: A Self-Improving AI Agent That Evolves Code Using Foundation Models and Real-World Benchmarks - MarkTechPost\",\"url\":\"https://www.marktechpost.com/2025/06/06/darwin-godel-machine-a-self-improving-ai-agent-that-evolves-code-using-foundation-models-and-real-world-benchmarks/\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving ...\",\"url\":\"https://blog.biocomm.ai/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/DGM.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/392204438_Darwin_Godel_Machine_Open-Ended_Evolution_of_Self-Improving_Agents\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.22954\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the Darwin Gödel Machine analysis:\n\n## Key Findings on Scaffolding vs. Magic\n\nThe system's current reliance on frozen foundation models means its ultimate capabilities are bounded by these models, and it doesn't yet learn to improve the foundation models themselves. This indicates that the improvements are heavily dependent on the base model's quality rather than representing \"magic\" self-improvement.\n\n## Performance Results on Benchmarks\n\nThe DGM automatically improved its coding capabilities over 80 iterations, achieving significant gains on two challenging benchmarks: SWE-bench improved from 20.0% to 50.0% success rate, and Polyglot improved from 14.2% to 30.7% on the full benchmark.\n\nImportantly, agents evolved using Claude 3.5 Sonnet transferred successfully to Claude 3.7 Sonnet (59.5% vs. base 19.0%) and o3-mini (33.0% vs. base 23.0%), showing that agents achieved 28.9% on Polyglot when evolved on SWE-bench (vs. base 14.2%). This demonstrates that improvements are indeed dependent on the specific base model and benchmark used.\n\n## Core Scaffolding Approach\n\nThe paper focuses on improving the design of coding agents with frozen pretrained foundation models (e.g., tool use, workflows). The system works through code modification and empirical evaluation rather than through fundamental breakthroughs—it's scaffolding improvements on top of existing models.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"efd74918-3649-41f2-96b7-a138dbc70e3e","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:16.549Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Darwin Godel Machine analysis scaffolding not magic depends on base model benchmark","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01SWfTRy3PTqavo2kgDmGk8a","content":[{"title":"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code","url":"https://sakana.ai/dgm/"},{"title":"Paper page - Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2505.22954"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML","url":"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine"},{"title":"The Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Improvement via Recursive Code Mutation and Empirical Fitness | by Adnan Masood, PhD. | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@adnanmasood/the-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-open-ended-improvement-via-recursive-code-mutation-and-empirical-fitness-a777681d73e4"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: A Self-Improving AI Agent That Evolves Code Using Foundation Models and Real-World Benchmarks - MarkTechPost","url":"https://www.marktechpost.com/2025/06/06/darwin-godel-machine-a-self-improving-ai-agent-that-evolves-code-using-foundation-models-and-real-world-benchmarks/"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving ...","url":"https://blog.biocomm.ai/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/DGM.pdf"},{"title":"(PDF) Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/392204438_Darwin_Godel_Machine_Open-Ended_Evolution_of_Self-Improving_Agents"},{"title":"Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.22954"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about the Darwin Gödel Machine analysis:\n\n## Key Findings on Scaffolding vs. Magic\n\nThe system's current reliance on frozen foundation models means its ultimate capabilities are bounded by these models, and it doesn't yet learn to improve the foundation models themselves. This indicates that the improvements are heavily dependent on the base model's quality rather than representing \"magic\" self-improvement.\n\n## Performance Results on Benchmarks\n\nThe DGM automatically improved its coding capabilities over 80 iterations, achieving significant gains on two challenging benchmarks: SWE-bench improved from 20.0% to 50.0% success rate, and Polyglot improved from 14.2% to 30.7% on the full benchmark.\n\nImportantly, agents evolved using Claude 3.5 Sonnet transferred successfully to Claude 3.7 Sonnet (59.5% vs. base 19.0%) and o3-mini (33.0% vs. base 23.0%), showing that agents achieved 28.9% on Polyglot when evolved on SWE-bench (vs. base 14.2%). This demonstrates that improvements are indeed dependent on the specific base model and benchmark used.\n\n## Core Scaffolding Approach\n\nThe paper focuses on improving the design of coding agents with frozen pretrained foundation models (e.g., tool use, workflows). The system works through code modification and empirical evaluation rather than through fundamental breakthroughs—it's scaffolding improvements on top of existing models."],"durationSeconds":9.346312125001102,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3120aeb4-7450-4ba3-ad54-baecbf5b8ed5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"11ba1554-54d1-414f-adc6-b94c5669e063","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"ae50cd09b1428afac","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E4qFXSwHwmFBECf1CPnJiH","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"self-improvement loop collapses without verifiable reward reward hacking drift\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Audited Skill-Graph Self-Improvement for Agentic LLMs via Verifiable Rewards, Experience Synthesis, and Continual Memory\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23760\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Improving AI Agents through Self-Play\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.02731\"},{\"title\":\"G-Zero: Self-Play for Open-Ended Generation from Zero Data\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2605.09959\"},{\"title\":\"Reward Hacking in Self-Improving Code Agents | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ikrQWGgxYg\"},{\"title\":\"Avoiding Reward Hacking\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/avoiding-reward-hacking\"},{\"title\":\"Reinforcement Learning from Meta-Evaluation: Aligning Language Models Without Ground-Truth Labels\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.21268\"},{\"title\":\"Spontaneous Reward Hacking in Iterative Self-Refinement\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/papers/2407.04549\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Improvement of Large Language Models: A Technical Overview and Future Outlook\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.25681\"},{\"title\":\"Adversarial Reward-Hacking\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/adversarial-reward-hacking\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found relevant research on this topic. Here's what the literature shows:\n\n## Self-Improvement Loop Challenges\n\nDeployed self-improvement loops face an operational security problem where optimization pressure, distribution shift, and imperfect observability create incentives for reward hacking, brittle specialization, and untraceable behavioral drift that is difficult to reproduce, audit, or govern.\n\n## The Reward Hacking Problem\n\nBecause any specified reward model is merely a proxy for complex human values, strong optimization pressure often leads to \"Goodhart's Law\" scenarios: when a measure becomes a target, it ceases to be a good measure. Reward hacking refers to a phenomenon where optimizing an imperfect proxy reward function leads to poor performance according to the true reward function.\n\n## Collapse and Drift\n\nA key finding is that a characteristic fingerprint of hacking is a regime where the true reward achieved under increasing optimization strength rises and then sharply collapses. Additionally, while initial gains appear strong, a late-stage collapse occurs where accuracy drops sharply even as reward continues to increase, which is known as reward hacking.\n\n## Solutions with Verifiable Rewards\n\nOne proposed approach treats self-improvement as iterative compilation of an agent into a growing directed skill graph whose promotions are gated by verifier-backed evidence, combining verifiable, decomposed rewards for tool-use correctness, outcome validity, skill reuse, and composition integrity.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"5184d2ea-34ae-4a13-99fd-11d117b0aa06","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:19.324Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"self-improvement loop collapses without verifiable reward reward hacking drift","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01NzKGSTWAyQJebCpBvTqUG5","content":[{"title":"Audited Skill-Graph Self-Improvement for Agentic LLMs via Verifiable Rewards, Experience Synthesis, and Continual Memory","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23760"},{"title":"Self-Improving AI Agents through Self-Play","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.02731"},{"title":"G-Zero: Self-Play for Open-Ended Generation from Zero Data","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2605.09959"},{"title":"Reward Hacking in Self-Improving Code Agents | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ikrQWGgxYg"},{"title":"Avoiding Reward Hacking","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/avoiding-reward-hacking"},{"title":"Reinforcement Learning from Meta-Evaluation: Aligning Language Models Without Ground-Truth Labels","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.21268"},{"title":"Spontaneous Reward Hacking in Iterative Self-Refinement","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/papers/2407.04549"},{"title":"Self-Improvement of Large Language Models: A Technical Overview and Future Outlook","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.25681"},{"title":"Adversarial Reward-Hacking","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/topics/adversarial-reward-hacking"}]},"Based on the search results, I found relevant research on this topic. Here's what the literature shows:\n\n## Self-Improvement Loop Challenges\n\nDeployed self-improvement loops face an operational security problem where optimization pressure, distribution shift, and imperfect observability create incentives for reward hacking, brittle specialization, and untraceable behavioral drift that is difficult to reproduce, audit, or govern.\n\n## The Reward Hacking Problem\n\nBecause any specified reward model is merely a proxy for complex human values, strong optimization pressure often leads to \"Goodhart's Law\" scenarios: when a measure becomes a target, it ceases to be a good measure. Reward hacking refers to a phenomenon where optimizing an imperfect proxy reward function leads to poor performance according to the true reward function.\n\n## Collapse and Drift\n\nA key finding is that a characteristic fingerprint of hacking is a regime where the true reward achieved under increasing optimization strength rises and then sharply collapses. Additionally, while initial gains appear strong, a late-stage collapse occurs where accuracy drops sharply even as reward continues to increase, which is known as reward hacking.\n\n## Solutions with Verifiable Rewards\n\nOne proposed approach treats self-improvement as iterative compilation of an agent into a growing directed skill graph whose promotions are gated by verifier-backed evidence, combining verifiable, decomposed rewards for tool-use correctness, outcome validity, skill reuse, and composition integrity."],"durationSeconds":11.613333000000566,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"11ba1554-54d1-414f-adc6-b94c5669e063","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
