{"parentUuid":"6b09636f-209a-47d5-967b-5f78103d255e","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ae50cd09b1428afac","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_013L4iCpVQs69YNsuQxaLWjX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018zVRAHJAu4H1R92773izCd","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://machine-learning-made-simple.medium.com/googles-alphaevolve-and-the-future-of-automated-discovery-6eb8033879dd","prompt":"Extract exact verbatim quotes about AlphaEvolve's core limitation: that it only works in domains with an automated/machine-evaluable evaluator, that it requires a programmatic evaluation function, and that it fails or is out of scope where solutions cannot be automatically scored. Give exact wording with quotation marks."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":451,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1172,"cache_read_input_tokens":21028,"output_tokens":471,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1172},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":451,"output_tokens":471,"cache_read_input_tokens":21028,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1172,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1172,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcG2Cze8vXX1H9K72jRUk","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"45d792a6-42d1-4caa-b2d5-7318824f9240","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:53.386Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"6b09636f-209a-47d5-967b-5f78103d255e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"96f7ce82-27af-4c04-ae02-270c4873a922","agentId":"ae50cd09b1428afac","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01G8Nf5PGQW6b45Nf8oA2uCw","type":"tool_result","content":"# Exact Quotes on Reward Hacking in Iterative Self-Refinement\n\n**On the core phenomenon:**\n\"reward hacking, where the evaluator's ratings improve while the generation quality remains stagnant or even decreases as judged by actual user preference\"\n\n**On shared model vulnerabilities:**\n\"the optimization pressure can drive them to exploit shared vulnerabilities\"\n\n**On empirical evidence of divergence:**\n\"iterative self-refinement leads to deviation between the LLM evaluator and human judgment, demonstrating that reward hacking can occur spontaneously in-context\"\n\n**On context sharing effects:**\n\"the severity of reward hacking is influenced by the context window length and whether the context is shared between the generator and evaluator\"\n\n**On practical risk:**\n\"Misaligned evaluations can lead to degeneration in true output quality while falsely indicating improvement\""}]},"uuid":"c613f830-a240-47b1-b2c5-7ce41a058a52","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:57.360Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":205292,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Exact Quotes on Reward Hacking in Iterative Self-Refinement\n\n**On the core phenomenon:**\n\"reward hacking, where the evaluator's ratings improve while the generation quality remains stagnant or even decreases as judged by actual user preference\"\n\n**On shared model vulnerabilities:**\n\"the optimization pressure can drive them to exploit shared vulnerabilities\"\n\n**On empirical evidence of divergence:**\n\"iterative self-refinement leads to deviation between the LLM evaluator and human judgment, demonstrating that reward hacking can occur spontaneously in-context\"\n\n**On context sharing effects:**\n\"the severity of reward hacking is influenced by the context window length and whether the context is shared between the generator and evaluator\"\n\n**On practical risk:**\n\"Misaligned evaluations can lead to degeneration in true output quality while falsely indicating improvement\"","durationMs":4853,"url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/papers/2407.04549"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6b09636f-209a-47d5-967b-5f78103d255e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"45d792a6-42d1-4caa-b2d5-7318824f9240","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"96f7ce82-27af-4c04-ae02-270c4873a922","agentId":"ae50cd09b1428afac","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018zVRAHJAu4H1R92773izCd","type":"tool_result","content":"# AlphaEvolve's Core Limitation: Automated Evaluation Requirement\n\nHere are the exact verbatim quotes about AlphaEvolve's dependence on machine-evaluable functions:\n\n**On the fundamental constraint:**\n\n\"If a domain has: 1. A code-based representation of potential solutions 2. A machine-gradeable evaluation function …then it is tractable for automated, scalable optimization.\"\n\n**On domains where it cannot operate:**\n\n\"If the problem can't be scored well, it can't be optimized.\"\n\n**On the evaluator as the critical gating factor:**\n\n\"This function is the system's _truth oracle_. It returns scalar scores: latency, accuracy, compression ratio, whatever defines success. If it can't be machine-evaluated, it doesn't count.\"\n\n**On scope limitations:**\n\n\"AlphaEvolve can only operate in **domains where evaluation can be formalized**. That includes math, systems optimization, hardware design, algorithm tuning. Not poetry, yet.\"\n\n**On the strategic bottleneck this creates:**\n\n\"The key is not to go back, but to build counter-balance systems that improve accessibility and grassroots layer adoption...the next arms race is not in building better agents — it's in building **better evaluation environments**.\"\n\nThese quotes collectively establish that **absence of an automated evaluator is the hard boundary** of AlphaEvolve's applicability."}]},"uuid":"a25f6086-ea05-498e-9bd3-2d10d161db2f","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:37:00.826Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":484334,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# AlphaEvolve's Core Limitation: Automated Evaluation Requirement\n\nHere are the exact verbatim quotes about AlphaEvolve's dependence on machine-evaluable functions:\n\n**On the fundamental constraint:**\n\n\"If a domain has: 1. A code-based representation of potential solutions 2. A machine-gradeable evaluation function …then it is tractable for automated, scalable optimization.\"\n\n**On domains where it cannot operate:**\n\n\"If the problem can't be scored well, it can't be optimized.\"\n\n**On the evaluator as the critical gating factor:**\n\n\"This function is the system's _truth oracle_. It returns scalar scores: latency, accuracy, compression ratio, whatever defines success. If it can't be machine-evaluated, it doesn't count.\"\n\n**On scope limitations:**\n\n\"AlphaEvolve can only operate in **domains where evaluation can be formalized**. That includes math, systems optimization, hardware design, algorithm tuning. Not poetry, yet.\"\n\n**On the strategic bottleneck this creates:**\n\n\"The key is not to go back, but to build counter-balance systems that improve accessibility and grassroots layer adoption...the next arms race is not in building better agents — it's in building **better evaluation environments**.\"\n\nThese quotes collectively establish that **absence of an automated evaluator is the hard boundary** of AlphaEvolve's applicability.","durationMs":6965,"url":"https://machine-learning-made-simple.medium.com/googles-alphaevolve-and-the-future-of-automated-discovery-6eb8033879dd"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"45d792a6-42d1-4caa-b2d5-7318824f9240","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
